OL,3,C'Site safety' worker 'avoided being
OL,4,Chit by train by two seconds' in near
OL,5,Cmiss
OL,7,FThe Rail Accident Investigation Branch
OL,8,F(RAIB) says workers arrived at 9.35am
OL,9,Fand were all briefed to stay at least
OL,10,Ftwo metres away from the tracks.
OL,12,FRecords show the signallar was
OL,13,Fcontacted at 9.49am to block the lines
OL,14,Fso the team could access the area they
OL,15,Fneeded to work on. This was done, with
OL,16,Fthe line handed back three minutes
OL,17,Flater.
OL,19,FOnce they reached the site, work began
OL,20,Fas planned and the group began to fix
OL,21,Ffaulty cables alongisde the track.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
