OL,3,C'Site safety' worker 'avoided being
OL,4,Chit by train by two seconds' in near
OL,5,Cmiss
OL,7,FHowever, the 'person in charge'
OL,8,Fnoticed that distance between the
OL,9,Ftracks and the area they were working
OL,10,Fon was becoming increasingly narrow.
OL,11,FThey continued up the track but asked
OL,12,Ffive others to remain back.
OL,14,FThe person moved out of the "safe
OL,15,Farea" and close to an open railway
OL,16,Fline - leaving them just 1.1 metres
OL,17,Faway from the track and at risk of
OL,18,Fbeing hit by a train.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
