OL,3,C'Site safety' worker 'avoided being
OL,4,Chit by train by two seconds' in near
OL,5,Cmiss
OL,7,FCCTV images show the London-bopund
OL,8,Ftrain approaching the worker at
OL,9,F10.44am after travelling around a
OL,10,Ftight bend.
OL,12,FOverhanging vegetation meant the
OL,13,Fworker was obscured from the driver's
OL,14,Fview until around five seconds before
OL,15,Fthe train reached them.
OL,17,FIt was at this point that the driver
OL,18,Fsounded a horn to warn of the train's
OL,19,Fapproach. It was travelling at 54mph
OL,20,Fat the time.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
