OL,5,Cmiss
OL,7,FIt was stated that 'the person in
OL,8,Fcharge' only realised they had been
OL,9,Finvolved in a near miss when the
OL,10,Fdriver of a later train asked them to
OL,11,Fcontact the signaller using a signal
OL,12,Fpost telephone.
OL,14,FIt was then discovered the signaller
OL,15,Fhad been trying to contact the workers
OL,16,Fwith no success due to poor phone
OL,17,Freception. The 'person in charge' was
OL,18,Falso not carrying the phone they had
OL,19,Fbeen issued with.
OL,21,FWhat did the investigation find?
